<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.5374.1.6>
    dc:creator "Moura, Ana B. G.", "Nazaré-Silva, Everton E.", "Silva, Fernando A. B." ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "A new species of Uroxys Westwood, 1842 (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Scarabaeinae) from central Brazil, and taxonomical remarks on Uroxys epipleuralis (Boucomont, 1928)" ;
    bibo:endPage "118" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2023-11-15" ;
    bibo:startPage "106" ;
    bibo:volume "5374" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151111>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151113>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151115>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151117>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151119> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151111>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Uroxys species. A–B, Uroxys epipleuralis (Boucomont, 1928), males; C–D, U. punctatus new species, holotype and paratype, respectively (C, male; D, female)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10151111/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151113>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Head and pronotum of Uroxys species. A–B, Uroxys epipleuralis (Boucomont, 1928), head, males; C–D, U. punctatus new species head (C male; D female); E–F, U. epipleuralis (Boucomont, 1928), pronotum, males; G–H, U. punctatus new species pronotum (G, male; H, female)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10151113/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151115>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. The male genitalia of two species of Uroxys epipleuralis (Boucomont, 1928) and U. punctatus new species. A–B, Uroxys epipleuralis tegmen (A, lateral view; B, dorsal view); C–D, U. punctatus tegmen (C, lateral view; D, dorsal view); E, U. epipleuralis superior and inferior portions of medial endophallite, ventral view; F, U. epipleuralis inferior portion of medial endophallite; G, U. punctatus inferior portion of medial endophallite; H, U. epipleuralis superior right peripheral (SRP) endophallites, complex of axial (A), subaxial (SA), and frontolateral peripheral (FLP) endophallites." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10151115/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151117>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Type specimens studied for this work. A, Choeridium epipleurale Boucomont, 1928 (currently, Uroxys epipleuralis), lectotype; B, U. thoracalis Balthasar, 1940, holotype; C, U. dureti Martínez, 1947, holotype. A and B courtesy of Fernando Z. Vaz-de-Mello; C courtesy of Mario Cupello." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10151117/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151119>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Known distribution of Uroxys epipleuralis (Boucomont, 1928) and U. punctatus new species." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10151119/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

